        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener><dateline><date when="1916-04-17">17 April 1916 .</dateline></date>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet</persName>:</salute></opener>
                <p>Thank you for your letter. I am returning the proof of <title key="pyrotechnics" level="a">"Pyrotechnics"</title> corrected.</p>
                <p>There is a mistake in the copy of <title key="patterns" level="a">"Patterns"</title>which you have. Somehow it was printed wrong in <persName  key="margaret_anderson">Margaret Anderson's</persName> <title key="littleReview" level= "j">book</title>, and from there copied wrong again. It is not very important, but I should prefer to have it right while you are about it:</p>
                <p>In the first line of the third stanza, your copy reads <quote type="english">“the splashing of waterdrops”</quote>; it should read <quote type="english">“the plashing of waterdrops”</quote>.</p>
                        <p>Will you please see that this correction is made and be an angel?</p>
                                <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
                            </p>
        </body>
        <back>
          <div type="notes">
              <note target="#n1" resp="mb"> <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet Monroe</persName> is reprinting <title key="patterns" level="a">"Patterns"</title> originally published in <title key="littleReview" level= "j">The Little Review</title> in her anthology.</note>
            </div> 
        </back>
